annotation.TEXT: So, here's Patchouli, and once again, it starts off fairly simple.
Space-time rewind count: 3
D'oh. I should've been able to avoid that one...

Okay, seriously, why is there an instant death pit there instead of the bounce/hurt blocks like usual? Maybe there was no real reason for me to backtrack there, but why kill me for being a little curious, instead of just hitting me for the usual 20 damage?
BGM: Yoshi's Island: SMW2 - Room Before Boss
Maybe, if I can get around the enemy-only blocks that are in the way...
Yep, that's what I've been told...
Ack! That muncher OMNOMNOM-ed a tiny corner of one of my shoes, which of course costs me 20 energy. Oh, but there's some power ups here, so I wonder if there's a boss just up ahead...
How did I not get hit by that bullet? I thought I ducked late, but I guess not.

Clunk! Huh, I guess there was only one Lava Lotus in that book. Oh, but I can still spin jump off of the book! I guess the top of the book is made up of special custom blocks that you can spin jump off of!

"BARF!" indeed. And, in addition to the usual bounce/hurt blocks being absent, what was the point in making that floor over there become non-solid when the switch is turned OFF in the first place? If it remained solid and I backtracked, I would've just hit a dead-end upon encountering a wall that I passed through earlier while the switch was ON, and that would've been that.
BGM: TH06 - Stage 3 - Shanghai Teahouse ~ Chinese Tea
Total donations made so far: 2000 point items.
And, now she's added fireballs into the mix.
Demo(?) count: 2
Ow. This still isn't too difficult, but I keep getting hit stupidly by the bullets spawning up there.
Bonk.

Yeah, that situation was a real mind-boggler. Anyway, to keep going with the level, I have to turn that switch OFF, then climb up here and go to the right, and not go in that other sinister direction!
Okay, I saw something change to the left when I hit that ON/OFF switch. I'm going to backtrack a bit to check it out, but it's probably nothing special.
At least the penalty for falling for that trick here is just the loss of some energy, instead of flat-out death!
So, I guess I gotta just dodge the book's shots while bouncing off of it to reach Patchouli. Okay, I should be able to handle that.
Yep, but why did it send me back here? And why wasn't the door labelled with a nearby "R" like usual?
Wow, those bullets and the paragoomba orb made that setup kind of tricky for a moment.
BGM: Touhou 10.5 - Septette for the Dead Princess
Well, at least the switches remained OFF. (Maybe the reset door sent me back to start in case I somehow screwed up while the switches were ON.)
BGM: TH06 - Locked Girl ~ The Girl's Secret Room
...Oh, what the heck was that? Okay, seriously. Let's actually try aiming for Patchouli this time!
Alright, it's boss time against Meiling herself! It starts out very simple, but I bet it'll get harder at some point!
Ack, I got boned.
Whoa, gotta be careful of the occasional fire magic around here.
And forget that one point item way down there that I missed. It's not worth losing 20 energy to get. (Now, if I'd get over 50 point items by sacrificing 20 energy, that would be worth it.)
Okay, this looks tricky...
Well, of course Patchy's gonna start shooting at me too. It wouldn't make sense for her to not take any actions herself.
BGM: TH06 - Stage 4 - Voile, the Magic Library
Umm... Forget about a couple of those point items. The muncher pillars make them way too tricky be worth going for.
So, am I at the mansion gates?
Interesting how I go behind the fence on the right. I guess that's to represent me going through the gate.
Hmm... I think I should fall here... maybe.
Ooh, point items, but they're guarded. Hmm...
And, after six stomps, she's sped up and started throwing horizontal projectiles.

Alright, so The Scarlet Devil wins it! However, I've been told that The Scarlet Devil is like a marathon level, where I'll have to go through multiple stages in a row, so first, I'm going to go to the Hakurei Shrine and make donations to top out my energy.
Argh! I can't believe I fell for that. I think Super Marina World pulled the exact same stunt somewhere, but I didn't fall for it there... (Maybe because it was more obvious there?)
Yes, Remilia's theme in the fighting games uses "Princess" instead of "Queen" in its title.

Hmm... Due to the low ceiling, I guess I can't stay on the moving platform the whole way. However, I certainly should stay near it, because I'll probably-- make that definitely-- need to ride it again.
So, here we are in what's basically a representation of stage 3 of EoSD, I guess.
There's another one of those dotted green blocks. I wonder if there's a switch palace to find at some point...
Wah! Let's try not to fall off the platform here...
Man, there sure are a lot of bullet-spewing spell circles around here. Oh, is that a point item arrow? Maybe I'm nearing the boss now?
Okay, that pattern's done. Huh, this one seems interesting...
BGM: TH06 - Shanghai Alice of Meiji 17
Oh, is that it for Meiling? Only two patterns? Well, I guess maybe that's because I have to go through multiple stages in a row in this level.
Gotta time these fairy maid stomps properly to avoid getting OMNOMNOM-ed by the OMNOMNOM-ers.
Obviously, I'm going to rewind out of this...
Looks similar to how the previous pattern ended, but the bullets' firing patterns are now trickier to deal with.
And, here come the bones!
I think the boss is up ahead...
Yay, I've maxed out my energy! I guess this means I was okay with stopping at 679 when I filled up at the shrine earlier.
Okay, I think I've got a good rhythm going here...
What the heck?! Patchouli's throwing bones now! That seems a bit... odd.
Replace "togheather" with "together".
Wow, that's a silly misspelling of "together", LOL!
Aha! That got me through safely. Ooh, there were power ups in there too. Nice.
Well, it doesn't appear that a boss is coming up just yet...
Bam, got 'em! However, the book graphic stays. I guess the book graphic is a harmless object, and the Lava Lotuses are invisible enemies overlapping the book.
Alright, here we go!
Bonk.
...Or not.
That's kind of neat.
Oh, since these are actually Lava Lotuses, can I kill them with the orb?

Now, I did PM Silver Scarlet on SMW Central about these videos of me playing Touhou Mario some time ago, and I got a reply saying she'd definitely be following my videos. So, it's up to her if she wants to comment, I guess.
Hello, and welcome back to Touhou Mario! Now, there are four levels left to pick from here. Which one will I be heading to today? Let's find out...
Monster combo! (10 hits)
Okay, in this pattern, Patchy's flying around throwing bones right from the start.
Whoops, can't go back that way.
What the...?!
Whoa, what's with the "VS" screen? Also, no actual dialogue like with Cirno and Rumia?
Hmm... Well, I guess 679 out of 699 should be enough. (I hope I don't later regret not maxing out completely here...)
Ten stomps cleared that pattern (and I did it perfectly). Now what's next?
Oh, so they're guarded up there, too... Still, I should be able to get through if I aim right...
Oh, interesting. So, are they like Thwomps?
Alright, so I guess I've gotta ride on this gray flying platform. And, doing so triggers the fast autoscroll on the background, as expected.
Ow, I totally got caught in a crossfire there...
Is this a reset door?
Looks like I'll need to spin jump off this book to reach those point items.
Hyper combo! (5 hits)
No, they're actually like Lava Lotuses. Alright, fair enough.
Super combo! (4 hits)
Nuts, don't be making stupid mistakes...
Argh! The two Lava Lotuses in that book are out of sync, which makes this more hazardous! Okay, forget trying to get every single one of those point items...
Of course, it would help if I didn't make dumb mistakes during the easy early part of the battle...

Oof! Well, that's interesting. I got hit just as that phase ended, so my HP only dropped by 4 from that last hit. And with that, Patchouli is beaten! However, what challenges await in the rest of the Scarlet Devil Mansion? Find out next time! To be continued...
And, we're dealing with this ON/OFF gimmick again.
Hello!
